#common errors are:
# 1. Syntax errors: These occur when the code violates the rules of the programming language. For example, missing parentheses or using incorrect indentation.
# 2. Name errors: These occur when a variable or function is referenced before it is defined or outside of its scope.
# 3. Type errors: These occur when an operation is performed on an object of an inappropriate type.
# 4. Index errors: These occur when trying to access an element in a sequence using an invalid index.
# 5. Attribute errors: These occur when trying to access an attribute or method that does not exist on an object.
# 6. Logic errors: These occur when the code does not produce the expected output due to incorrect logic or algorithm.
# 7. File errors: These occur when there are issues with opening, reading, or writing files.
# 8. Import errors: These occur when there are issues with importing modules or packages.
# 9. Runtime errors: These occur during the execution of the program and can be caused by various factors such as division by zero or memory errors.
# 10. Exception handling errors: These occur when errors are not properly handled using try-except blocks.
# 11. Memory errors: These occur when there is insufficient memory available to run the program.
# 12.KeyError Error: This error is raised when a key is not found in a dictionary.
# 13.ValueError Error: This error is raised when a value is not found in a sequence.